g clogged or draining slowly? We will provide professional sewer and drain cleanings for both residential and commercial clientele.\r\n\r\n<strong>Yard or Sprinkler Leaks:</strong>\r\n\r\nOne of the hidden costs of increased water / utility bills is a leaky sprinkler line. Fixing this can help you reduce water usage. Our professionals can locate and repair your yard leak so that you are no longer washing water down the curb.\r\n\r\n<strong>Repair or Replace Faucets:</strong>\r\n\r\nFaucets, faucets, faucets. The typical home has several faucets so repair or replacement is often just a matter of time. We will complete all plumbing repairs faucets inside and out, including your kitchen sink. Should you need a new faucet installed, we will also gladly be at your service.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>','Services','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-2','','','2013-05-08 19:45:25','2013-05-08 19:45:25','',10,'http://prontoplumbingdfw.com/10-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(11,88889,'2011-09-23 18:09:06','2011-09-23 18:09:06','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-31\" title=\"our-plumbing-advantage\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://prontoplumbingdfw.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/our-plumbing-advantage.jpg\" width=\"310\" height=\"150\" />There\'s no substitute for <strong>experience</strong> when it comes to plumbing. Some of the best learning experiences are the ones that were the most difficult to figure out.  This experience has given us a level of tenacity that is unmatched when it comes to diagnosing and repairing your plumbing issue. No matter how large or small your plumbing project may be, our professionals will provide you with an accurate quote that will always be competitive and contain no hidden costs or fees.\r\n\r\n<strong>Our Additional Services Include:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Drain &amp; Sewer Cleaning</li>\r\n	<li>Yard &amp; Sprinkler Leaks</li>\r\n	<li>Water, Sewer &amp; Gas Line Repairs/Replacements</li>\r\n	<li>Water Heater Repairs &amp; Installations</li>\r\n	<li>Plumbing Remodels</li>\r\n	<li>Garbage Disposal Replacements</li>\r\n	<li>Sewer &amp; Water Line Testing</li>\r\n	<li>Faucet Pipe Inspections</li>\r\n	<li>Faucet Repairs/Replacements</li>\r\n	<li>Water &amp; Sewer Line Location</li>\r\n</ul>','Our Advantage','','publish','open','open','','our-advantage','','','2013-05-08 19:50:16','2013-05-08 19:50:16','',0,'http://clearprofiles.com/plumbing101/?page_id=9',0,'page','',0),(12,88889,'2011-09-23 18:09:58','2011-09-23 18:09:58','Q. <strong>Should I use chemical drain cleaners?</strong>\n\nA. No. Most retail drain cleaners are harmful to your plumbing. Over time these products can corrode the inner lining of drain pipes. Call us to properly clean out your drains, we will be happy to assist you.\n\n<strong>Q. What is a leak detection Service?</strong>\n\nA. This is a specialized service intended to find hidden leaks underground and under foundations, utilizing state of the art sound detection devices. These ultra-sonic leak detection devices are the most effective method to promptly and efficiently find your leak source. We will determine the precise location of your leak and solve the problem as soon as possible.\n\n<strong>Q. Why does my water heater run out of hot water so quickly?</strong>\n\nA. There may be nothing wrong with your water heater. It may actually be that your faucets and shower heads are the problem source. Some older shower heads put out up to 5 gallons per minute. Newer shower heads only allow around 2.5 gallons of volume per minute. Switching to lower volume shower heads and faucets may solve the problem. Another problem may be that your water heaters\' dip tube needs to be replaced. If you are experiencing this problem, please do not hesitate to contact us to resolve the problem.\n\n<strong>Q. What is causing my water heater to leak water?</strong>\n\nA. The most common cause of water leaks from your water heater would be a rusted out tank. This would require you to replace the entire water heater. If your water heater is not near the end of the manufacturers’ life estimate your problem may be from a source that is much simpler and less of a financial strain. For example, the pressure relief valve, usually located at the top of the unit, could be leaking. You can be rest-assured that our expertly trained technicians will promptly diagnose your leak problem and suggest a solution that will be in your best interest.\n\n<strong>Q. Why does my toilet keep refilling?</strong>\n\nA. There are many reasons for a toilet that constantly runs. It could be a that flapper isn\'t seating properly. The flapper can accumulate a thin layer of scale or a slippery film over time which can cause the water seal to fail. Replacing the flapper will correct this problem. Another cause can be a kinked or tangled lift chain which is easily fixed as well. If neither of these is the problem, it could be a worn out flush valve. Our professionals will have your water wasting toilet repaired in no time.\n\n<strong>Q. Why is my electric water heater not heating?</strong>\n\nA. In many cases the cause for your water heater not heating properly is a tripped high-temperature cutoff. This can be fixed by simply pressing the reset button. If that doesn\'t work it could be a faulty heating element. If that is the case you must replace the element.\n<strong>Q. How do I choose the right water heater for my home?</strong>\n\nA. Choosing the right water heater depends on a number of factors that include: the number of people in your household, number of bathtubs and/or showers, whether your home has a dishwasher, washing machine or whirlpool bathtub, and whether your water heater is a natural gas or electric unit. Typically, for a family of 4, a 50 gallon gas water heater will be sufficient for your needs. If your water heater is electric you would want to consider a 50-60 gallon unit. Please contact us to ensure the unit you choose will serve your needs.\n\n<strong>Q. What is meant by the terms \"hard water\" and \"soft water\"?</strong>\n\nA. \"Hard water\" is water that contains high levels of calcium and/or magnesium. The presence of these minerals in high amounts can result in deposits, called scale, on appliances and fixtures and can negatively affect their performance over time. Hard water can also decrease the cleansing action of soaps and detergents you use in cleaning our dishes, clothing and in bathing by creating films on surfaces instead of dissipating the soaps and detergents for maximum effectiveness. Having a water softening system installed in your home will essentially eliminate calcium and magnesium through interaction with sodium through a process called ion exchange.\n\n<strong>Q. Why do my water pipes rattle?</strong>\n\nA. The problem may be that water lines are not properly isolated from the structural elements of your home. If this is the case, the motion of water moving through the pipes may be transferring to beams, joists or studs in or beneath your flooring or in the walls. If the pipes are accessible the solution may be as simple as inserting an insulating material between the pipes and the structural elements they are touching. If your pipes only rattle when the water is turned on or off it may be that you need to install a water hammer arrester that will eliminate the jolt caused by quick closing water valves. This problem is not always easy to diagnose and you should always rely on a plumbing professional to accurately diagnose your rattling pipe problem.\n\n<strong>Q. I live in the Dallas area. Do you service my area?</strong>\n\nA. Absolutely! we are happy to serve the Dallas area including the cities of Allen, Carrollton, Dallas, Farmers Branch, Garland, Irving, Mesquite, Plano, Richardson, Rockwall, Rowlett,  Wylie among others. If you have any questions regarding your address, please contact us.','FAQs','','publish','open','open','','faqs','','','2011-09-23 18:09:58','2011-09-23 18:09:58','',0,'http://clearprofiles.com/plumbing101/?page_id=11',0,'page','',0),(13,88889,'2011-09-23 18:10:09','2011-09-23 18:10:09','<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h1>Pronto Plumbing:  (972) 989-5880</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Contact','','publish','open','open','','contact','','','2012-08-08 12:07:51','2012-08-08 12:07:51','',0,'http://clearprofiles.com/plumbing101/?page_id=13',0,'page','',0),(20,88889,'2011-09-23 18:17:12','2011-09-23 18:17:12','Most slab leaks can be accessed without destruction to your floors or walls. We are here to take the stress out of your slab leak dilemma. Before our process ever begins, we will ensure that you are fully knowledgeable of our process so that you can have the peace of mind that your leak problem will soon be resolved.\n\nBelow you will find a brief description of tunneling and concrete penetration, and the processes we utilize to repair your slab leak. If you have any questions please do not hesitate to ask. Our specialists are here for you.\n\n<strong>Tunneling:</strong>\n\nTunneling is a process used to access lines in need of repair. By tunneling underneath the foundation you prevent any cosmetic or collateral damage to the interior of the house.\n\n<strong>Slab Penetrations:</strong>\n\nPenetrating concrete slabs can be a real nightmare if you have not employed a licensed plumber whose expertise is slab leak repair. The noise of jack hammers can be overbearing but more often than not very necessary. We will explore all reasonable solutions to prevent the noise, dust , and debris so that your home is as normal as possible during our process. All considerations will be taken and your home will be treated as if it were our own. We work with precise care so that you do not have any additional costs related to your leak repair project.\n\n<strong>Piping Repair &amp; Replacement:</strong>\n\nPiping can sometimes be rerouted overhead in an attic, through a wall, or around the house outside underground. We explore those options to see if its feasable for your leak repair.','Slab Repair','','publish','open','open','','slab-repair','','','2011-09-23 18:17:12','2011-09-23 18:17:12','',10,'http://clearprofiles.com/plumbing101/?page_id=20',0,'page','',0),(22,88889,'2011-09-23 18:17:53','2011-09-23 18:17:53','You may be asking yourself, \"What causes a leak?\"\nBelow you will find some of the most common reasons why leaks happen.\n\n1. Changes in Water Chemistry &amp; Chemical Water Compositions\n2. Addition of Chemicals During the Water Treatment Process\n3. Substandard Piping &amp; Poor Workmanship\n4. \"Aggressive Water\", (This includes factors such as pH content, presence of chlorides, metal ions, and dissolved gases in the water)\n5. Electrolysis A Leaky pipe can also create an unhealthy environment for mold and mildew to thrive within the home. Of course another factor to keep in mind is the probability that most insurance companies will either raise your premium rates or issue a non-renewal notice to a homeowner who has leaky pipes.\n\nProtect yourself, your family and checkbook today!\n\nAccording to recent statistics, the majority of leaks reported were in the cold water and horizontal copper tubing. This means that most were under the concrete slab. Detecting leaks below the slab requires specialized equipment and experience.\n\nWe use high quality ground sensor equipment, sound amplifiers, and stereo headphones to locate leaks within inches of the pinholes. Sewer leaks are located by hydrostatic sewer test isolation and occassionally with assitance of a video camera.\n\nWhen leaks are found, immediately repairing the leak must be considered. We will ensure that not only will we find the source of your leak but that your leak will be professionally repaired so to prevent further damage. Please tour our leak repair page for a full explanation of our leak repair process. If you have any questions or would like to schedule a free estimate, please do not hesitate to contact us.','Leak Detection','','publish'